HEADWORD: Trifolium
<hw>Tri*fo"li*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
clover.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of leguminous herbs with
densely spiked flowers and usually trifoliate leaves; trefoil. There are
many species, all of which are called <xex>clover</xex>. See
<er>Clover</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

